{"TopicId":52760,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.0.5] Surface Mounted Stock-Alike Lights for Self-Illumination (v1.2.2 - 11/15/15)","CreatedByName":"Why485","CreatedById":26795,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-11T21:24:22Z","PageNum":9,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"hvacengi","CreatedById":124987,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-06T13:10:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222564559\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462523388\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155445\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022IgorZ\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, IgorZ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022padding-left:2em;margin-top:0px;color:rgb(51,51,51);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, \u0027Segoe UI\u0027, Arial, freesans, sans-serif, \u0027Apple Color Emoji\u0027, \u0027Segoe UI Emoji\u0027, \u0027Segoe UI Symbol\u0027;font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:25.6px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n[Internal] Migrate spot and omny lights to the stock LightModule.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n... snip ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022padding-left:2em;margin-top:0px;color:rgb(51,51,51);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, \u0027Segoe UI\u0027, Arial, freesans, sans-serif, \u0027Apple Color Emoji\u0027, \u0027Segoe UI Emoji\u0027, \u0027Segoe UI Symbol\u0027;font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:25.6px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n[Internal] Drop unused SurfaceLight module.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t dropping the previous module mean that the light\u0027s lens color does not change with the light\u0027s color?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"meyerweb","CreatedById":135212,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-06T14:11:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222564521\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462520786\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155445\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022IgorZ\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, IgorZ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThese lights are physics parts so, technically they can affect craft behavior. Did you place the parts symmetrically?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u2019s a single light, but the problem turns out not to have anything to do with either SurfaceLights or kOS.\u00A0 I had inadvertently created a permanent yaw trim with a keyboard shortcut to open the AnyRes mod.\u00A0 \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/124987-hvacengi/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022124987\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/124987-hvacengi/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@hvacengi\u003C/a\u003E figured it out for me over in the kOS thread, and provided a fix:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrim is set by pressing the modifier key (alt on windows) and one of the translation controls. \u00A0You can reset it using the modifier key and \u0022x\u0022. \u00A0This is not a control listed in the KSP settings, but you can find it on the KSP wiki. \u00A0I verified that on the save file provided [Alt]\u002B[X] stopped the errant yaw.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry for the errant bug report!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jacke","CreatedById":103694,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-06T15:32:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222564952\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462543890\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022135212\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022meyerweb\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, meyerweb said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u2019s a single light, but the problem turns out not to have anything to do with either SurfaceLights or kOS.\u00A0 I had inadvertently created a permanent yaw trim with a keyboard shortcut to open the AnyRes mod.\u00A0 \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/124987-hvacengi/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022124987\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/124987-hvacengi/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@hvacengi\u003C/a\u003E figured it out for me over in the kOS thread, and provided a fix:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry for the errant bug report!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not hard to get these keyboard control collisions, as well as have problems with inadvertent trim.\u00A0 (Trim is very useful in fine aircraft and rocket control. As well, the new Unity 5 UI helps by making the stock attitude control needles in the lower left larger and easier to read by default.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s because another common source of issues is that in KSP, functions linked to [Key] will also be triggered on pressing [Mod]\u002B[Key] (in addition to the functions linked to [Mod]\u002B[Key]); in other words on Windows, pressing Alt-[Key] also acts as if [Key] was pressed.\u00A0 For example, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57146-sarbian/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257146\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57146-sarbian/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sarbian\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s excellent \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/83821-110-gcmonitor-143-a-graphic-memory-monitor-may-1st/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EGCMonitor\u003C/a\u003E toggles the display of its control window with Alt-F1.\u00A0 This issue means bringing up and dismissing GCMonitor\u0027s window by pressing Alt-F1 twice also creates two screenshots, just as if F1 was pressed twice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo inadvertently triggering multiple actions is not just a problem with functions with the same keypress, it\u0027s also functions with similar keypresses differing only by whether they include using [Mod].\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JeffreyCor","CreatedById":93167,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-06T15:39:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222564861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462540225\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022124987\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022hvacengi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, hvacengi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t dropping the previous module mean that the light\u0027s lens color does not change with the light\u0027s color?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would imagine so, as this was the reason the module was created in place of using the stock system.:( But given the choice of losing surface lights entirely or losing the feature, I chose losing the feature \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E Unless the stock system changed, I haven\u0027t tried anything with lights yet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-06T18:03:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222564861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462540225\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022124987\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022hvacengi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, hvacengi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t dropping the previous module mean that the light\u0027s lens color does not change with the light\u0027s color?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222565135\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462549186\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002293167\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JeffreyCor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, JeffreyCor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would imagine so, as this was the reason the module was created in place of using the stock system.:( But given the choice of losing surface lights entirely or losing the feature, I chose losing the feature \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E Unless the stock system changed, I haven\u0027t tried anything with lights yet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nColors still can be changed. Light color was always in the stock light module but in 1.0.5 it was not available via UI. Now , when it\u0027s available for the stock lights the original module of this mod looses its benefits.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/aCBMKFk.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022aCBMKFk.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-06T19:55:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222564861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462540225\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022124987\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022hvacengi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, hvacengi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t dropping the previous module mean that the light\u0027s lens color does not change with the light\u0027s color?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry, I misunderstood your comment about the len\u0027s. Yeah, len\u0027s coloring will gone. I missed it when was deprecating the module. Never used coloring, though. Created a regression \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ihsoft/SurfaceLights/issues/2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ebug\u003C/a\u003E. Shouldn\u0027t be a problem to bring it back for omni and spot lights, but 4-way is a problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"hvacengi","CreatedById":124987,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-06T20:00:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222565708\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462564543\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155445\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022IgorZ\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, IgorZ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry, I misunderstood your comment about the len\u0027s. Yeah, len\u0027s coloring will gone. I missed it when was deprecating the module. Never used coloring, though. Created a regression \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ihsoft/SurfaceLights/issues/2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ebug\u003C/a\u003E. Shouldn\u0027t be a problem to bring it back for omni and spot lights, but 4-way is a problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGlad you caught that, I sat down to type it up an make you an image explaining it and then got tied up here at work. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs an alternative, kOS is intending to\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eeventually\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0(Maybe this makes it as good a time as any) expose out our kOSLightModule (the thing that backs the light effects on our processors and the cherry light) for external use. \u00A0It is able to do the same thing, so you could make a MM patch to add our module if that\u0027s installed. \u00A0(I say that, however for some reason my testing earlier didn\u0027t work, so I have to figure out an exact patch).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JeffreyCor","CreatedById":93167,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-06T23:10:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222565488\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462557820\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155445\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022IgorZ\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, IgorZ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nColors still can be changed. Light color was always in the stock light module but in 1.0.5 it was not available via UI. Now , when it\u0027s available for the stock lights the original module of this mod looses its benefits.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EReveal hidden contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022aCBMKFk.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/aCBMKFk.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou misunderstand. In stock the light emitted changes color, but the light itself remains white (just tested with a stock light). What the plug in did was allowed the light to match the light emitted. Thus a red light emotion setting would cause the light itself to be red, not a white light with red light illuminating off of it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Which I see I was beaten to pointing this out \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-06T23:12:51Z\u0022 title=\u002205/06/2016 11:12  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 6, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by JeffreyCor\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stone Blue","CreatedById":77721,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-07T00:10:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222566099\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462576216\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002293167\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JeffreyCor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, JeffreyCor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou misunderstand. In stock the light emitted changes color, but the light itself remains white (just tested with a stock light). What the plug in did was allowed the light to match the light emitted. Thus a red light emotion setting would cause the light itself to be red, not a white light with red light illuminating off of it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Which I see I was beaten to pointing this out \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPardon my ignorance, as I\u0027m no coder or modeller, but cant you just make separate textures for the lens part of the light, each a different color to match the light emitted color choices, and just use the Firespitter or B9 texture switch in a .cfg to automatically switch the lens texture to the light emitted color?\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThis seems to be pretty much what the AviationLights/Deadskins textures do...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-07T00:11:42Z\u0022 title=\u002205/07/2016 12:11  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 7, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Stone Blue\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-07T08:21:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222566209\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462579829\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277721\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Stone Blue\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Stone Blue said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPardon my ignorance, as I\u0027m no coder or modeller, but cant you just make separate textures for the lens part of the light, each a different color to match the light emitted color choices, and just use the Firespitter or B9 texture switch in a .cfg to automatically switch the lens texture to the light emitted color?\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThis seems to be pretty much what the AviationLights/Deadskins textures do...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nColor is made of three components, each ranges from \u00600.0\u0060 to \u00601.0\u0060. How many textures do you think will cover all the values? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stone Blue","CreatedById":77721,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-07T14:29:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222566691\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462609272\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155445\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022IgorZ\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, IgorZ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nColor is made of three components, each ranges from \u00600.0\u0060 to \u00601.0\u0060. How many textures do you think will cover all the values? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI realise you assign the emitted colors with sliders, but what about textures just for a few base colors?... They wont match the emitted light exactly, but a red for reddish, blue for blueish, green for greenish, yellow for yellowish, and white for whiteish.... So maybe 5 or 6 textures?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-07T23:05:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222566995\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462631360\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277721\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Stone Blue\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Stone Blue said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI realise you assign the emitted colors with sliders, but what about textures just for a few base colors?... They wont match the emitted light exactly, but a red for reddish, blue for blueish, green for greenish, yellow for yellowish, and white for whiteish.... So maybe 5 or 6 textures?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt may be a good workaround for 4-way light. I still hope to find a better solution. The other lights are working fine with changed emissive color.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-08T08:58:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nv1.2.3 alpha 3 \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ihsoft/SurfaceLights/releases/tag/1.2.3.alpha3\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eis available\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCumulative updates from the stock version:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n[Change] Minor code adjustments to compile under KSP 1.1\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Change] Disable animation on 4-way light since it doesn\u0027t work properly anyways.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Change] Rename GUI action and event names in 4-way light to identify which light they control.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Internal] Create a multipoint light module and use it in 4-way light.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Internal] Migrate spot and omny lights to the stock LightModule.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Internal] Drop incomplete SurfaceNavLight module.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Internal] Drop unused SurfaceLight module.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Internal] Rename multi point light module to a more KSP name.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Internal] Improve reliability of multi point light module when config paremetrs or model are bad.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Internal] Create a new module based on old SurfaceLight to support colored lens on the light.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Change] Expose setting \u0022Lens brightness\u0022 to allow customizing light\u0027s minimum brightness level.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nThis state I consider stable. If not major complains arise on the release I\u0027ll start a new forum topic and try to upload the new version on CKAN.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/ts3Ctee.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022ts3Ctee.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-08T08:59:41Z\u0022 title=\u002205/08/2016 08:59  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 8, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by IgorZ\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Booots","CreatedById":62446,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-08T15:05:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat looks great! Is it possible to get a MM patch to make the stock lights use this system so their lenses change colour too?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Svm420","CreatedById":136047,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-08T15:13:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAwesome! Thanks for the update.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn a side note. The Navlight module you removed from the code. What state was it in? I had been hoping Why485 would have had in in a working condition considering the thread he posted \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/125544-wip105-surface-nav-lights/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-08T18:20:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222568957\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462719917\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002262446\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Booots\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Booots said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat looks great! Is it possible to get a MM patch to make the stock lights use this system so their lenses change colour too?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tried to replace module on the stock lights but it didn\u0027t work. Changing of the emission color on the material just has no effect. I have a theory that it gets overridden in the animation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222568977\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462720418\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022136047\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Svm420\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Svm420 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAwesome! Thanks for the update.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn a side note. The Navlight module you removed from the code. What state was it in? I had been hoping Why485 would have had in in a working condition considering the thread he posted \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/125544-wip105-surface-nav-lights/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo be honest, I have no idea on the state of this module. I tried to figure out what was the idea behind it and eventually gave up. Though, now with this link I at least have some idea of what was it. May be I\u0027ll get back it it. Restoring the deleted module is a trivial task.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lajoswinkler","CreatedById":79159,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-09T15:07:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is a really nice mod, essential to me because stock lights are clunky and not nice. These look stock, but aren\u0027t in the way and look much better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Enceos","CreatedById":110725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-09T17:19:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155445-igorz/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022155445\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155445-igorz/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@IgorZ\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0and \u003Cstrong\u003E@Everyone\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0There\u0027s a cool and simple\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://spacedock.info/mod/552/Bulb\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EB.U.L.B.\u003C/a\u003E mod by Mr.\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110959-alshain/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022110959\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110959-alshain/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Alshain\u003C/a\u003E, which enables the stock light module to have RGB sliders in flight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-09T17:21:21Z\u0022 title=\u002205/09/2016 05:21  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 9, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Enceos\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-09T17:41:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222571233\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462814394\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Enceos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n36 minutes ago, Enceos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155445-igorz/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022155445\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155445-igorz/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@IgorZ\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0and \u003Cstrong\u003E@Everyone\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0There\u0027s a cool and simple\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://spacedock.info/mod/552/Bulb\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EB.U.L.B.\u003C/a\u003E mod by Mr.\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110959-alshain/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022110959\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110959-alshain/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Alshain\u003C/a\u003E, which enables the stock light module to have RGB sliders in flight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm, they use the same approach which I tried:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Eemi\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Ematerial\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003ESetColor\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E(\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022str\u0022\u003E\u0022_EmissiveColor\u0022\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E,\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022kwd\u0022\u003Enew\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EColor\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E(\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Ered\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E,\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E green\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E,\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E blue\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E,\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022lit\u0022\u003E1\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E));\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt didn\u0027t work for the stock lights. Will check it again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-09T17:56:29Z\u0022 title=\u002205/09/2016 05:56  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 9, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by IgorZ\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Enceos","CreatedById":110725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-10T02:34:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222571275\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timest