span\u003EColor\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E(\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Ered\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E,\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E green\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E,\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E blue\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E,\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022lit\u0022\u003E1\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E));\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt didn\u0027t work for the stock lights. Will check it again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s how WBILight does it: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Angel-125/WildBlueTools/blob/master/Parts/WBILight.cs\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Angel-125/WildBlueTools/blob/master/Parts/WBILight.cs\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-10T04:23:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110725-enceos/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022110725\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110725-enceos/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Enceos\u003C/a\u003E \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/106975-angel-125/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022106975\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/106975-angel-125/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Angel-125\u003C/a\u003E,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGuys, have you \u003Cstrong\u003Eactually\u003C/strong\u003E tried to apply this technique on the \u003Cem\u003Estock\u003C/em\u003E lights? In \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ihsoft/SurfaceLights/blob/1.2.3.alpha3/Source/ModuleColoredLensLight.cs#L62\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EModuleColoredLensLight\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0I use exactly the same approach as you suggest but it just \u003Cem\u003Edoes not \u003C/em\u003Ework on the stock lights.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222571233\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002252760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462814394\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Enceos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, Enceos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155445-igorz/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022155445\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155445-igorz/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@IgorZ\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0and \u003Cstrong\u003E@Everyone\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0There\u0027s a cool and simple\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://spacedock.info/mod/552/Bulb\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EB.U.L.B.\u003C/a\u003E mod by Mr.\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110959-alshain/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022110959\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110959-alshain/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Alshain\u003C/a\u003E, which enables the stock light module to have RGB sliders in flight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBtw, this mod does light color and material emissive color updates in every \u0060Update()\u0060 call. If your craft has many lights of this kind the performance can suffer significantly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-10T04:33:47Z\u0022 title=\u002205/10/2016 04:33  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 10, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by IgorZ\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Enceos","CreatedById":110725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-10T04:52:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/106975-angel-125/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022106975\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/106975-angel-125/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Angel-125\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0I haven\u0027t looked, but I presume there\u0027s a fundamental difference between the models of your lights and the models of the stock lights. Which is why \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#0000FF;\u0022\u003EWBILight\u003C/span\u003E doesn\u0027t work on stock models. Do you think there\u0027s a workaround to enable your module on the stock lights?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-14T05:16:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGiven there were no major complains or bugs for the alpha 3 I did a release. here is the new topic:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/139724-112-surface-mounted-stock-alike-lights-for-self-illumination-v123-051316/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure of this topic should be requested for the close or left open \u0022just in case\u0022. Suggestions?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Frybert","CreatedById":97766,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-29T14:02:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLocked for above reason.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}